 Legal matters that the program is not available to handle are referred to appropriate agencies.    *Misuse of the SLS may result in a violation of the UIC Standards of Conduct.       Request an Appointment   Upon arrival for an appointment with a SLS attorney, students must bring their current UIC ID Card and a copy of their current registration schedule .  Request an appointment with our office, by emailing studentlegalservices@uic.edu, to understand more about how we can help you with the below:       Student Legal Subpages -- temporary until the content is ready     Working with us   Understand how Student Legal Services assists students and how to prepare for an appointment     Housing Law   Know your rights about rental/land lord agreements     Immigration Law   Find answers on undocumented status, DACA, employment visas, and more, from Immigration Attorneys       Family and Divorce Law   Seek assistance with simple family law matters     Employment Agreements   Work with SLS to fully understand employment contracts before signing     Criminal Records Erasure   Learn how previous criminal records may be eligible for expungement     Tips for International Students   Understand common legal issues for UIC’s International student population     Other Services   Find out about our other services, including help with simple contracts or traffic violations                      UIC Logo        Office of the Dean of Students         DOS Offices    Career Services    Student Employment    Counseling Center    Wellness Center      For Employees    SA Human Resources    SA Technology    Leave Management    The Pulse      Safety    UIC Police    Office of Access & Equity    Contact-US    Giving         Contact   1200 West Harrison St., 3030 SSB Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-4857  dos@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Jo